Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-Only Tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
        return;
    }

    // Registry access code...
}
```

Or filter at run time: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=WindowsOnly"`

In **MSTest v3+**, use a condition attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[SupportedOSPlatform("windows")]
public void RegistryTest() { /* ... */ }
```

## 2. Skip in CI (Requires Local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuRenderTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
        return;
    }

    // GPU test logic...
}
```

Then in CI pipelines: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky External API — Retry

In **MSTest v3+**, use the built-in `[Retry]` attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApiFlakyTest()
{
    var result = CallWeatherApi();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

For **MSTest v2**, implement manual retry or use `[TestCategory("Flaky")]` to isolate:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("Flaky")]
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    Exception? last = null;
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
    {
        try
        {
            var result = CallWeatherApi();
            Assert.IsNotNull(result);
            return; // passed
        }
        catch (Exception ex) { last = ex; }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Failed after 3 attempts: {last!.Message}");
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Even on Failure

Use `[TestCleanup]` — it runs **regardless** of test outcome:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = string.Empty;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessTempFileTest()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        // Even if this throws, Cleanup still runs
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

---

**Summary table:**

| Scenario | MSTest v2 | MSTest v3+ |
|----------|-----------|------------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + filter | `[SupportedOSPlatform]` |
| Skip in CI | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + env check | Same, or custom condition attribute |
| Flaky/retry | Manual loop or category filter | `[Retry(N)]` |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` | `[TestCleanup]` |
